<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2056) demonstrated that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: A recent study (Smith &amp; Brown, 2056) demonstrated that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
When the authors are referred to more than once in the same paragraph do not include the date in 
subsequent references, as long as the work cannot be confused with others cited.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	In a recent study, Smith and Brown (2056) demonstrated that&hellip; Smith and Brown also 
	found that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation, use quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2056) observed that &#34;the organism&#8217;s chemical defence was remarkable&#34; 
	(p. 56).
	<br>
	Alternatively: Tests showed that &#34;the organism&#8217;s chemical defence was remarkable&#34; 
	(Smith &amp; Brown, 2056, p. 56).
</blockquote>
